content.rendered:
Barrel racing standings, presented by the Women’s Professional Rodeo Association (WPRA). Let’s get you started with the current 2021 World Standings in Barrel Racing.

Watch NFR 2023 Live Online - SUBSCRIBE HERE

NFR 2023 Streaming info
Streaming
The Cowboy Channel (real-time) Watch Here
RFD-TV (real-time) Watch Here
Cowboy Channel Plus (International) Watch Here

 

Barrel Racing poses a competition like no other. Hailey Kinsel is currently ranked No.1, and she will be looking to add her four World Championship this year to make it her first since 2015. The primary challenger is no other than Jordon Briggs and she will try as much as possible to win her third straight World Title.

Nine-time NFR qualifier Derrick Begay is teaming up with 12-time NFR cowboy Brady Minor. The other duo joining forces in Vegas is Quinn Kesler, a three-time NFR qualifying header and last year’s third place finisher in Arlington, Texas, Joseph Harrison.

The unofficial standings are published by WPRA and PRCA, they can change information any time if needed.
